cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on learning patch descriptors for image retrieval, which is a task related to computer vision and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses unsupervised learning methods, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on standard benchmarks, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
